@startuml event-driven-signal-flow-multiplayer
!theme plain
!include ../shared/theme.puml
!include ../shared/sequence-theme.puml

title Event-Driven Signal Flow: Multiplayer Synchronization

participant "CardManager\n(local rules)" as CM
participant "MultiplayerCardManager\n(sync extension)" as MCM
participant "GDSync" as Sync
participant "LocalServerSignaling\n(web patch path)" as LSS
participant "Signaling Server\n(HTTP/SSE relay)" as Relay
participant "Remote Client" as Remote

CM -> MCM : super() returns to override
MCM -> MCM : determine sync action\n(card_moved / entered_buffer / left_buffer)
MCM -> Sync : GDSync.call_func(\nsync_card_moved, [...])
Sync -> LSS : route packet via patched LocalServer (web)
LSS -> Relay : HTTP broadcast / enqueue
Relay -> Remote : SSE event (game_packet)
Remote -> Remote : apply synchronized state\n(move card, update visibility)

note right of MCM
Multiplayer logic extends local rules
by adding authority-managed sync calls.
end note

@enduml
